# fm_description / view_robot.launch.py — ROS graph for publishing robot state.
# joint_state_publisher turns panel commands into joint states;
# robot_state_publisher turns those into TF and republishes the URDF. A viz client
# (RViz or foxglove_bridge) subscribes these topics, launched separately. Nodes are
# plum boxes, topics cream pills. Arrow into a node = subscribe; out = publish.
# Where /robot_description itself comes from is the robot_state_publisher diagram.
...@styles
direction: right

jcmd: /joint_command { class: topic }
jsp: "joint_state_publisher(_gui)" { class: node }
js: /joint_states { class: topic }
rsp: robot_state_publisher { class: node }
tf: /tf { class: topic }
tfs: /tf_static { class: topic }
rd: /robot_description { class: topic }

jcmd -> jsp
jsp -> js
js -> rsp
rsp -> tf
rsp -> tfs
rsp -> rd
